{
  "texts": [
    "Mainstream technologies such as SVM and CNN are mentioned and applied.",
    "Taking CNN as an example, Kasapbaşi et al. [124] proposed a CNN-based human-computer interface for American Sign Language recognition, which achieved high accuracy and demonstrated excellent prediction in tested datasets.",
    "Musthafa et al. [125] developed an innovative gesture-based sign language recognition system that can automatically detect sign language and recognize various complex gestures and actions.",
    "The model applies CNN and image processing methods to determine fingertip positions in static images and convert them to text, which can identify photos of signers taken in real time.",
    "Alani et al. [126] addressed the ArSL-CNN model to train a variety of Arabic sign languages and achieved an overall accuracy of 97.29%."
  ]
}